The hypothesis might even serve to explain the conveyance of the treatise to England, if we suppose that Alexander transmitted a copy to his predecessor in his Irish diocese and that somebody copied it again on the way thither 3 and, as we have seen, there are some slight indications that matters Irish were ex- pected to be of interest to the reader of the exposition.
